Author: Nassim Nicholas Taleb
My Review:
Enjoyable Read

This is a book which has some interesting albeit repetitive content. In my opinion it lacks fluency. Hence the three stars.

The opinions are strong and make sense but the diatribes and coining of terms and insults do not flow. I have no issue with the content but I hated the presentation. A little attention to sentence structure would go a long way.

The preponderance of trite phrase often tempted me to lay the book aside. If it was not for the author’s reputation I would not have persisted in completing the book. The sentence structures really galled!

My Review:
mesmerizing read

This book showed me a world that we can all aspire to live in. For me it has dispelled the dystopian outlook of an aging sick population pointing to a hopeful future where elders potentially are not looked upon as a burden but are healthy members of society cherished for their accumulated knowledge.

I kinda knew what we could do with regard to diet, exercise and supplements. This book reinforced those concepts.
